You could do as Kris suggests and write plugins for Heritrix having it 
make decisions on-the-fly about what to write to disk.  But I&#39;d advise 
that learning java is a significant undertaking.  

I&#39;d suggest you begin by figuring heritrix, learning how to configure it 
to do a targetted crawl, and spend your time initially on the parsing of 
the downloaded ARCs (Take a look at Tom&#39;s pretty libarc tool if c/c++ is 
what you&#39;re used to).  Taking this approach will help you better 
determine the mods you want to make to heritrix, if you need to make 
them at all.

